City of Johannesburg mayor, Mpho Phalatse. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng CoGTA MEC Lebogang Maile has asked Johannesburg mayor Mpho Phalatse for a report on the disputed employment status of some municipal workers. The permanent appointment of 130 employees was rescinded following a recent council decision. Maile says Phalatse has seven days to give him a comprehensive report. He is concerned that the dispute may cause instability in the municipality and affect services to Joburg residents.